00:24:45.660 --> 00:24:48.210
And while people are
forming their questions,

00:24:48.210 --> 00:24:53.700
Kelsey, I wanted to go
again to the practical tips,

00:24:53.700 --> 00:24:57.840
because literally knowing
what to do can be a barrier.

00:24:57.840 --> 00:24:58.950
And I know--

00:24:58.950 --> 00:25:01.440
I mean, I'm embarrassed to say
even having read your book,

00:25:01.440 --> 00:25:03.750
I have two sympathy
cards sitting in my bag

00:25:03.750 --> 00:25:05.820
that I should have
sent weeks ago.

00:25:05.820 --> 00:25:10.380
And sometimes it just gets hard.

00:25:10.380 --> 00:25:12.930
So some practical
tips on how do we

00:25:12.930 --> 00:25:16.200
get ourselves to show up for the
people who need us in the way

00:25:16.200 --> 00:25:17.812
that they need us to.

00:25:17.812 --> 00:25:19.770
KELSEY CROWE: Well, first
even, a practical tip

00:25:19.770 --> 00:25:21.478
around those sympathy
cards, which we all

00:25:21.478 --> 00:25:22.950
know that experience--

00:25:22.950 --> 00:25:24.330
oh, I can't find the stamp.

00:25:24.330 --> 00:25:27.210
How do I get their
physical address?

00:25:27.210 --> 00:25:30.270
There's no expiration
date on condolences.

00:25:30.270 --> 00:25:33.780
So you said that
it's way too late.

00:25:33.780 --> 00:25:37.350
This is where it is a gift
to be a procrastinator,

00:25:37.350 --> 00:25:41.160
because very often, that person
who's grieving has heard a lot

00:25:41.160 --> 00:25:45.690
of condolences in the initial
aftermath-- and you know this--

00:25:45.690 --> 00:25:47.820
and then there are crickets.

00:25:47.820 --> 00:25:49.560
And you are actually
still sitting

00:25:49.560 --> 00:25:55.680
with this pretty deeply, if not
even more deeply, months later,

00:25:55.680 --> 00:25:59.340
and you don't even know if
it's appropriate to bring up

00:25:59.340 --> 00:26:00.840
the fact that you're
still grieving.

00:26:00.840 --> 00:26:06.010
So getting a card later in
that process is a total gift.

00:26:06.010 --> 00:26:08.382
So you could just pretend
that you meant it that way.

00:26:08.382 --> 00:26:10.110
[LAUGHTER]

00:26:10.110 --> 00:26:13.170
Or, of course, to send an email.

00:26:13.170 --> 00:26:16.770
Something that I do
as a practical tip,

00:26:16.770 --> 00:26:18.620
if somebody is going
through something--

00:26:18.620 --> 00:26:21.220
and even a positive thing--

00:26:21.220 --> 00:26:23.160
I put a little note
in my calendar,

00:26:23.160 --> 00:26:24.750
just a little
reminder-- don't forget

00:26:24.750 --> 00:26:28.200
to send the card that
day, something like that.

00:26:28.200 --> 00:26:31.080
And they keep toggling
you until you do it.

00:26:31.080 --> 00:26:35.940
But there really is very
rarely an expiration date

00:26:35.940 --> 00:26:36.720
on giving comfort.

